Reviews.Title: Solid cable at a solid price
Reviews.Author: Paul McGinley "Paul"
Reviews.Content: Makes installing analog cameras a breeze. I had an extremely long run with no power available locally and this solved the issue. Great picture quality and no interference. I would definitely buy it again.

Reviews.Title: Purchased 2 of these and both quit working
Reviews.Author: dlytle75
Reviews.Content: I purchased two of these cables for my QSee system.  Both of them worked great when I first installed them.  After about a month for each of them, they both stopped working.  One of the cables doesn't provide electrical power to the camera now, and the other one gets power but does not carry the video.  A great buy for the month it worked.  Not sure why they both stopped working.

Reviews.Title: Good shielded RG-59 coax with 2C #18 power wires.
Reviews.Author: David Johnson
Reviews.Content: Good cable, well constructed. Even though the photo shows a single cable it really is a siamese cable with RG-59 coax and a 2C #18 power cable. As a bonus it even came with a BNC coupling.It's shielded so the signal won't degrade over long distances, and it will shield against interference better.

Reviews.Title: Very Good
Reviews.Author: Tony
Reviews.Content: Overall this wire is great but when I ordered it I did not get working wire. I think the connections were loose therefore I returned it. However, I own 100ft with the same brand that works flawlessly.

Reviews.Title: Works very well. No distortion see
Reviews.Author: amazon "Sdog"
Reviews.Content: I have multiple Swann security units, that I use at various apartments buildings I have.  In some cases, I needed to run lines over 100 feet. I tried other cables I seemed to get some distortion. But not with these. even at 200',  I cannot tell the difference between this line/camera verse only 10' cable run lines.  The clarity on my monitors (both locally and remotely over the internet) look the same. The price is definitely fair. I have since purchased 12 of these 200' Q-See cables and have not had a problem with a single one of them.

Reviews.Title: Excellent Product/Excellent Price/Excellent Service
Reviews.Author: BO
Reviews.Content: The title says it all. The cable was delivered within a week and came exactly as described. All related parts were included and it was completely compatible with my Q-See surveillance system being installed at the same time. It was priced on Amazon far lower than the retail price for the same product on the Q-See.com website and, because I ordered several cables of shorter length at the same time; delivery was free at the time of purchase.

Reviews.Title: Q-See 200 Ft with Connectors
Reviews.Author: Jeffrey A. Holley
Reviews.Content: Worked well and easy to hookup. Heavier than the cable that came with the cameras.  I would recommend purchasing the cable.

Reviews.Title: Very Good Product
Reviews.Author: Track Timer
Reviews.Content: We use this cable with a FAT timing system for track and field. Very nice quality. I would buy this product again if I ever need additional cable..

Reviews.Title: Nice cables great shielding
Reviews.Author: Barbaqued
Reviews.Content: We use Qsee cameras all over our shop floor for security and process monitoring. We recently added some new equipment that played havoc with our regular cable causing all kinds of static on our monitors. These cables with shielding solved the problem

Reviews.Title: Couldn't be better.
Reviews.Author: SDB
Reviews.Content: I'm extremely happy with these cables.  The sheathing is thick & the connectors are heavy & well molded onto the ends.  They're not likely to pull off in any type of normal use.  I currently have 8 of the 200' cables & 3 of the 100' cables in use on my home security system.  I had some cheaper cables on some of my cameras but had ghosting problems with them.  These cables took care of that for good.  Amazon's price on the 200' cables is as good as anywhere else I've found.  I highly recommend them if you're looking for a quality cable & want to do it right the first time.  You won't be disappointed.

Reviews.Title: Kool Kat
Reviews.Author: Kathy Lynn Hines "Kool Kat"
Reviews.Content: I wanted a camera at back of my shed without trying to add cable after cable.This does the job.Works great.Has all the hook ups for the Q see cameras.It is heavy duty and will work with the weather.I am very happy they finally made a cable like this.I don't get the wireless cameras because too many people wrote how they interfere with the router(wifi).Love the cable.Highly recommend this cable for a long reach.

Shielded 200 Ft. Video & Power BNC(M) - BNC(M) Cable
High Quality Connectors
Use Indoor or Outdoor - Can Be Installed In-Wall
